{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597741539,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0MTc2MDAwMjU="},"target":"b0f23f6d3ca96c3ad74a095e8321806bd36bad66c959632c5d92a8bd3e1c7557","message":"Sorry to bother you again, but I was able to push the limits even further: it's now 70% faster and provides excellent biases for all tested hash lengths. https://github.com/avaneev/prvhash\n\nIt is a bit incomprehensible now, but I understand it pretty well, though not on high statistics level.\n\nI've removed `prvhash82` as it does not offer any realistic benefits now.\n\nEndianness-correction is now built-in.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597799197,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlRWRpdDo0MTc5NTkxMTE="},"target":"b0f23f6d3ca96c3ad74a095e8321806bd36bad66c959632c5d92a8bd3e1c7557","message":"Sorry to bother you again, but I was able to push the limits even further: it's now 70% faster and provides excellent biases for all tested hash lengths. https://github.com/avaneev/prvhash\n\nIt is a bit incomprehensible now, but I understand it pretty well, though not on high statistics level.\n\nI've removed `prvhash82` as it does not offer any realistic benefits now.\n\nEndianness-correction is now built-in.\n\nPlease also update the size of the function - it's now about 30 instructions longer.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597758645,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NTQ5MDY3OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-675490679"},"message":"It's also usable on 32-bit platform with 64-bit math emulation - only 40% slower.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597848127,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NjQ2OTQ4Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-676469487"},"message":"On a side note, PRVRNG64 passes `PractRand` 1 TB threshold with only several \"unusual\" evaluations. Probably, it's the first TRNG in the world. This claim requires evaluations from independent researchers.\n\n```\nRNG_test using PractRand version 0.95\nRNG = PRVRNG64, seed = 0xd2c6e844\ntest set = core, folding = standard (16 bit)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 512 megabytes (2^29 bytes), time= 2.6 seconds\n  no anomalies in 185 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 1 gigabyte (2^30 bytes), time= 5.2 seconds\n  no anomalies in 198 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 2 gigabytes (2^31 bytes), time= 10.1 seconds\n  no anomalies in 210 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 4 gigabytes (2^32 bytes), time= 19.8 seconds\n  Test Name                         Raw       Processed     Evaluation\n  [Low4/16]FPF-14+6/16:all          R=  +4.9  p =  4.7e-4   unusual          \n  ...and 221 test result(s) without anomalies\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 8 gigabytes (2^33 bytes), time= 41.8 seconds\n  no anomalies in 233 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 16 gigabytes (2^34 bytes), time= 85.8 seconds\n  no anomalies in 244 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 32 gigabytes (2^35 bytes), time= 166 seconds\n  no anomalies in 255 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 64 gigabytes (2^36 bytes), time= 349 seconds\n  no anomalies in 266 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 128 gigabytes (2^37 bytes), time= 708 seconds\n  no anomalies in 277 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 256 gigabytes (2^38 bytes), time= 1349 seconds\n  no anomalies in 288 test result(s)\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 512 gigabytes (2^39 bytes), time= 2791 seconds\n  Test Name                         Raw       Processed     Evaluation\n  [Low4/16]BCFN(2+3,13-0,T)         R=  +9.5  p =  1.2e-4   unusual          \n  ...and 297 test result(s) without anomalies\n\nrng=PRVRNG64, seed=0xd2c6e844\nlength= 1 terabyte (2^40 bytes), time= 5641 seconds\n  no anomalies in 308 test result(s)\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1597850738,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NjQ5NDg3MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-676494871"},"message":"\u003e On a side note, PRVRNG64 passes `PractRand` 1 TB threshold with only several \"unusual\" evaluations. Probably, it's the first TRNG in the world. This claim requires evaluations from independent researchers.\n\u003e \n\n@avaneev, Please take a look at [SHISHA](https://espadrine.github.io/blog/posts/shishua-the-fastest-prng-in-the-world.html):\n\u003e [...]\n\u003e Then, passing 32 tebibytes of PractRand was very hard.\n\u003e\n\u003e But once I reached that point, I realized that speed was going to be an issue. It wasn’t just about having a construction that \n\u003e emitted ten megabytes a second, taking a month to pass PractRand.\n\u003e [...]","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597850929,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NjQ5NjY3OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-676496678"},"message":"It's not PRNG, it's TRNG. There's a huge difference.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597851184,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NjQ5OTA2Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-676499063"},"message":"You see the pattern in the PractRang results. It's \"unusual\" at 4 GB and OK at 256 GB, \"unusual\" at 512 GB, and OK at 1 GB. Completely different math. I would extrapolate it will pass any threshold, I just do not have time to wait so long.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1597852482,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3NjUxMDM3OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/138#issuecomment-676510378"},"message":"I wouldn't want to get into a discussion about terminology, but TRNG can't be constructed algorithmically apriori.\n\nIn addition, to talk about large periods, you should prove that there are no cycles in your generator, at least for some subset of initial seeds. For instance, take look at [wyrand](https://github.com/wangyi-fudan/wyhash/blob/d15d6e7ebee5f408e362ba171708b00a4bb52574/wyhash.h#L118): it has an obvious period of 2^64 and a fairly understandable statistical skew due to the non-injectivity of the MUM transformation.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1597852482,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0MjQxNTQz"},"target":"0d0a443acf057798511e2087158c82adad80bc2a52643d5e515b9f79db951429","message":"I wouldn't want to get into a discussion about terminology, but TRNG can't be constructed (solely) algorithmically apriori.\n\nIn addition, to talk about large periods, you should prove that there are no cycles in your generator, at least for some subset of initial seeds. For instance, take look at [wyrand](https://github.com/wangyi-fudan/wyhash/blob/d15d6e7ebee5f408e362ba171708b00a4bb52574/wyhash.h#L118): it has an obvious period of 2^64 and a fairly understandable statistical skew due to the non-injectivity of the MUM transformation.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"173f4fceac25ce053a133bd829b18be7ad10b908"},"timestamp":1597852613,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0MjQyMTYx"},"target":"0d0a443acf057798511e2087158c82adad80bc2a52643d5e515b9f79db951429","message":"I wouldn't want to get into a discussion about terminology, but TRNG can't be constructed (solely) algorithmically apriori.\n\nIn addition, to talk about large periods, you should prove that there are no cycles in your generator, at least for some subset of initial seeds. For instance, take look at [wyrand](https://github.com/wangyi-fudan/wyhash/blob/d15d6e7ebee5f408e362ba171708b00a4bb52574/wyhash.h#L118): it has an obvious period of 2^64 and a fairly understandable statistical skew due to the non-injectivity of the MUM transformation.\n\n@wangyi-fudan, @lemire, FYI.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597939175,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3Nzc1Mjk0NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-677752944"},"message":"I actually use this test to generate default seed, it works pretty well. I generate 1 billion bytes with my hash function and evaluate the resulting statistic. Seed that results in 1.0 is pretty good overall.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1597950137,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3Nzg0MzA4Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-677843083"},"message":"Can you also provide the code for it? Just the basics, no integration needed","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597971823,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3Nzk4MDYyMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-677980621"},"message":"```\ndouble Counts[ 256 ] = { 0.0 };\n\n...for all hashes:\nuint64_t Hash = \u003cvalue\u003e;\nint j;\n\nfor( j = 0; j \u003c 8; j++ )\n{\nCounts[ (uint8_t) Hash ]++;\nHash \u003e\u003e= 8;\n}\n... then, finally:\ndouble Avg = 0.0;\n\nfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n{\n\tAvg += Counts[ i ];\n}\n\nAvg /= 256.0;\ndouble devsq = 0.0;\n\nfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n{\n\tconst double d = Counts[ i ] / Avg - 1.0;\n\tdevsq += d * d;\n}\n\ndev *= Avg / 256.0;\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597971823,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0Njc1Nzk2"},"target":"4df70962ae3851499e3ef0fa4324ec1af7433a8949db315c67de204744498ba1","message":"```\ndouble Counts[ 256 ] = { 0.0 };\n\n...for all hashes:\nuint64_t Hash = \u003cvalue\u003e;\nint j;\n\nfor( j = 0; j \u003c 8; j++ )\n{\n\tCounts[ (uint8_t) Hash ]++;\n\tHash \u003e\u003e= 8;\n}\n... then, finally:\ndouble Avg = 0.0;\n\nfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n{\n\tAvg += Counts[ i ];\n}\n\nAvg /= 256.0;\ndouble devsq = 0.0;\n\nfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n{\n\tconst double d = Counts[ i ] / Avg - 1.0;\n\tdevsq += d * d;\n}\n\ndevsq *= Avg / 256.0;\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597972177,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3Nzk4MjM5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-677982393"},"message":"Note that both `CryptGenRandom` on Windows and /dev/random on Unix have this statistic close to 1.0, rarely in the range 0.8-1.2. LCG random generators... not so much.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597972177,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0Njc2NjUy"},"target":"f1d934fd5a028aa2fe61694059a30267e2268e2e49be78be17d84e7c14f3e40b","message":"Note that both `CryptGenRandom` on Windows and `/dev/random` on Unix have this statistic close to 1.0, rarely in the range 0.8-1.2. LCG random generators... not so much.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597972967,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3Nzk4NTg3NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-677985875"},"message":"Here's a complete program to evaluate system RNG.\n```\n//$ lib \"win*|AdvAPI32\"\n\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n#include \u003cstdint.h\u003e\n#include \u003cmath.h\u003e\n\n#if defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\t#include \u003cwindows.h\u003e\n\t#include \u003cwincrypt.h\u003e\n#else // defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\t#define _UNIX 1\n#endif // defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\n#if defined( _UNIX )\n\tFILE* f; ///\u003c /dev/random file.\n#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\tHCRYPTPROV prov; ///\u003c Crypt provider (for Windows).\n#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\nint main()\n{\n\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tf = fopen( \"/dev/random\", \"rb\" );\n\n\t\tif( f == NULL )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\treturn( 1 );\n\t\t}\n\n\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tif( !CryptAcquireContext( \u0026prov, NULL, NULL, PROV_RSA_FULL,\n\t\t\tCRYPT_VERIFYCONTEXT ))\n\t\t{\n\t\t\treturn( 1 );\n\t\t}\n\n\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\tint l;\n\n\tfor( l = 0; l \u003c 100; l++ )\n\t{\n\t\tdouble Counts[ 256 ] = { 0.0 };\n\t\tuint64_t i;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c ( 1LL \u003c\u003c 24LL ); i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tuint8_t val = 0;\n\n\t\t\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\t\tfread( \u0026val, 1, 1, f );\n\n\t\t\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\t\tCryptGenRandom( prov, 1, \u0026val );\n\n\t\t\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\tCounts[ val ]++;\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdouble Avg = 0.0;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tAvg += Counts[ i ];\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tAvg /= 256.0;\n\t\tdouble dev = 0.0;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tCounts[ i ] /= Avg;\n\t\t\tdouble d = Counts[ i ] - 1.0;\n\t\t\tdev += d * d;\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdev *= Avg / 256.0;\n\n\t\tprintf( \"iter %i dev1 %f\\n\", l, fabs( 1.0 - dev ));\n\t}\n\n\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tfclose( f );\n\n\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tCryptReleaseContext( prov, 0 );\n\n\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n}\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597972967,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0Njc4Njgz"},"target":"1af280a962b1a00deab8750c9957867f09271f64496b451172daafb196cebda3","message":"Here's a complete program to evaluate system RNG.\n```\n//$ lib \"win*|AdvAPI32\"\n\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n#include \u003cstdint.h\u003e\n#include \u003cmath.h\u003e\n\n#if defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\t#include \u003cwindows.h\u003e\n\t#include \u003cwincrypt.h\u003e\n#else // defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\t#define _UNIX 1\n#endif // defined( _WIN32 ) || defined( _WIN64 )\n\n#if defined( _UNIX )\n\tFILE* f; ///\u003c /dev/random file.\n#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\tHCRYPTPROV prov; ///\u003c Crypt provider (for Windows).\n#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\nint main()\n{\n\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tf = fopen( \"/dev/random\", \"rb\" );\n\n\t\tif( f == NULL )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\treturn( 1 );\n\t\t}\n\n\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tif( !CryptAcquireContext( \u0026prov, NULL, NULL, PROV_RSA_FULL,\n\t\t\tCRYPT_VERIFYCONTEXT ))\n\t\t{\n\t\t\treturn( 1 );\n\t\t}\n\n\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\tint l;\n\n\tfor( l = 0; l \u003c 100; l++ )\n\t{\n\t\tdouble Counts[ 256 ] = { 0.0 };\n\t\tuint64_t i;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c ( 1LL \u003c\u003c 24LL ); i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tuint8_t val = 0;\n\n\t\t\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\t\tfread( \u0026val, 1, 1, f );\n\n\t\t\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\t\tCryptGenRandom( prov, 1, \u0026val );\n\n\t\t\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\t\tCounts[ val ]++;\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdouble Avg = 0.0;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tAvg += Counts[ i ];\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tAvg /= 256.0;\n\t\tdouble devsq = 0.0;\n\n\t\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c 256; i++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdouble d = Counts[ i ] / Avg - 1.0;\n\t\t\tdevsq += d * d;\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tdevsq *= Avg / 256.0;\n\n\t\tprintf( \"iter %i dev1 %f\\n\", l, fabs( 1.0 - devsq ));\n\t}\n\n\t#if defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tfclose( f );\n\n\t#else // defined( _UNIX )\n\n\t\tCryptReleaseContext( prov, 0 );\n\n\t#endif // defined( _UNIX )\n}\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597984686,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODAyNzkzNw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678027937"},"message":"Here's also a cool experimental program to find adequate LCG generators. But LCG, of course, fails normalcy test, can't reach 0.8 - 0.12 value range.\n\n[findlcg.txt](https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/files/5106756/findlcg.txt)","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597984686,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0NzA5NjAz"},"target":"193c7c577a61c48116206d59c4d796a00f5c4534bbdbdf242067df332c11d368","message":"Here's also a cool experimental program to find adequate LCG generators. But LCG, of course, fails normalcy test, can't reach 0.8 - 0.12 value range (it will pass normalcy test only if its upper 8-bits of output are used).\n\n[findlcg.txt](https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/files/5106756/findlcg.txt)","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597984410,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODAzMjY1MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678032651"},"message":"If you use only upper 8-bits of such LCG output, it will pass PractRand tests up to 1 GB.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597998717,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODAzODMxMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678038312"},"message":"LCG can be easily upgraded to pass beyond 1GB in PractRand. Example LCG which passes 16 GB threshold if upper 8-bits of output are used on each round. (the values were also found via `findlcg.txt` above, but with an added xorshift).\n```\nconst uint64_t lcg1 = 6449002856053061667ULL;\nconst uint64_t lcg2 = 2168563226064687862ULL;\nuint64_t Seed = 9104992244502867339ULL;\n...\nSeed = Seed * lcg1 + lcg2;\nSeed ^= Seed \u003e\u003e 32;\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597998717,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0NzUzMTI4"},"target":"a99ff4aee973b3a560691c42d5c3ff693ee98aba5becb6484cca500e98396afe","message":"LCG can be easily upgraded to pass beyond 1GB in PractRand. Example LCG which passes 64 GB threshold if only upper 32 bits of Seed are used on each round. (The values were also found via `findlcg.txt` above, but with an added xorshift).\n```\nconst uint64_t lcg1 = 6449002856053061667ULL;\nconst uint64_t lcg2 = 2168563226064687862ULL;\nuint64_t Seed = 9104992244502867339ULL;\n...\nSeed = Seed * lcg1 + lcg2;\nSeed ^= Seed \u003e\u003e 32;\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597999014,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0NzU0MTkx"},"target":"a99ff4aee973b3a560691c42d5c3ff693ee98aba5becb6484cca500e98396afe","message":"LCG can be easily upgraded to pass beyond 1GB in PractRand. Example LCG which passes 128 GB threshold if only upper 32 bits of Seed are used on each round. (The values were also found via `findlcg.txt` above, but with an added xorshift).\n```\nconst uint64_t lcg1 = 6449002856053061667ULL;\nconst uint64_t lcg2 = 2168563226064687862ULL;\nuint64_t Seed = 9104992244502867339ULL;\n...\nSeed = Seed * lcg1 + lcg2;\nSeed ^= Seed \u003e\u003e 32;\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597999074,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODA0MDAzNw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678040037"},"message":"This is based on pre-defined seeds, may not work with random seeds. This is not as effective as PRVHASH which outputs random 4 bytes per round, without dependency on the seed value.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597999074,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0NzU0Mzk3"},"target":"bde6c3af5992d3d0483a4e8f45b51cb97207d64fe5c9dcc78c6e49666c2464e4","message":"This is based on pre-defined seeds, may not work with random seeds. This is not as effective as PRVHASH which works without dependency on the seed value.","files":null},{"type":5,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1598002612,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDM2Nzg4MjU5MzU="},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1598083282,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODQ2NTgzMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678465832"},"message":"I don't see the value of using sliced double bytes as counters. \nThere are 11 high exponent bits (mainly the first hash byte + 3 more), plus 53 less important mantissa bits. The avg is certainly not around 1.0. But maybe I'm missing something.\nThe very first hash byte dominates everything.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1598083282,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk0OTcwMzEx"},"target":"a8bfdb63a7513306e05237e8a987e28795994aaefde5ebcacc0efb4efb63a90d","message":"I don't see the value of using sliced double bytes as counters. \nThere are 11 high exponent bits (mainly the first hash byte + 3 more), plus 53 less important mantissa bits. The avg is certainly not around 1.0. But maybe I'm missing something.\nThe very first hash byte dominates everything.\n\nSee the `bitfreq` branch","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598092069,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODYyMzcyMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678623720"},"message":"This is an incorrect implementation: the counting should go for all hashes in a set, not for individual hashes.\n\nYou can replace Counts with uint64_t - it's not a problem. Only Avg requires double.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598092322,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODYyNDA2OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678624069"},"message":"So, the part with if (diff \u003e 0.4) should be performed after for (uint32_t seed = 0; seed \u003c 1\u003c\u003c31; seed += 8) {} loop.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598126252,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODY4NjA5MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678686091"},"message":"\"Good\" is probably diff \u003c 0.1.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598126336,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODY4NjI1NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678686255"},"message":"(diff \u003e 0.4) is not too restrictive for fail, it should be (diff \u003e 0.3), any good random number generator will pass this.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1598132159,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODY5NzcxNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678697716"},"message":"Problem is that the best hashes fail with \u003e= 0.47.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598178546,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODc1Njg4MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678756881"},"message":"But the implementation is incorrect in your bitfreq branch. If they fail given a correct counting implementation, it means their bit frequencies are not normally-distributed, they are far from what good random number generators.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598178546,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUyODU5"},"target":"9597858d32d4f9cb94676a032504b332e2d330077850848289f59173f2a41388","message":"But the implementation is incorrect in your bitfreq branch. If they fail given a correct counting implementation, it means their bit frequencies are not normally-distributed, they are far from what good random number generators produce.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179082,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODc1NzY3Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678757677"},"message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.7: `too uniform`; if dev\u003e1.3: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.1: `perfect`.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179082,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUzMzAw"},"target":"9175a01f1c44fd45b9b1b196ea84224dfa3ed9ade0c35154d765b7cb5f5d8597","message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.7: `too uniform`; if dev\u003e1.3: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.1: `perfect`, otherwise `good`.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179200,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUzMzc3"},"target":"9175a01f1c44fd45b9b1b196ea84224dfa3ed9ade0c35154d765b7cb5f5d8597","message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.7: `overly uniform`; if dev\u003e1.3: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.1: `perfect`, otherwise `good`.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179347,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUzNTA5"},"target":"9175a01f1c44fd45b9b1b196ea84224dfa3ed9ade0c35154d765b7cb5f5d8597","message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.75: `overly uniform`; if dev\u003e1.25: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.1: `perfect`, otherwise `good`.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179411,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUzNTUx"},"target":"9175a01f1c44fd45b9b1b196ea84224dfa3ed9ade0c35154d765b7cb5f5d8597","message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.7: `overly uniform`; if dev\u003e1.3: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.1: `perfect`, otherwise `good`.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179427,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDUzNTY1"},"target":"9175a01f1c44fd45b9b1b196ea84224dfa3ed9ade0c35154d765b7cb5f5d8597","message":"Instead of using `fabs( 1.0 - dev )` estimate, use simply `dev` estimate, and do not fail the test in any outcome: simply print if dev\u003c0.7: `overly uniform`; if dev\u003e1.3: `non-uniform`; if fabs( 1.0 - dev )\u003c0.15: `perfect`, otherwise `good`.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598179331,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODc1ODA5Mg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678758092"},"message":"This estimate is useful at proving cryptographic properties. `perfect` and `good` are cryptographic quality.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598198844,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODc5MjQ3Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-678792477"},"message":"This commit is still incorrect. The part:\n```\nhashtype hashval;\n  hash(text,len,seed,\u0026hashval);\n\n  memset (counts, 0, sizeof (counts));\n  for( int j = 0; j \u003c sizeof(hashtype); j++ )\n  {\n    uint8_t b;\n    memcpy (\u0026b, \u0026hashval, 1);\n    counts[ b ]++;\n    hashval \u003e\u003e= 8;\n  }\n```\nshould be inside the `for (uint32_t seed = 0; seed \u003c 1\u003c\u003c31; seed += 8) {}` loop. Everything else should be outside of this loop.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598198844,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk1MDcyNzEw"},"target":"c0c4ba42dc1056d42adfee473999904386eb5b0e45067991818e697cbc68604a","message":"This commit is still incorrect. The part:\n```\nhashtype hashval;\n  hash(text,len,seed,\u0026hashval);\n\n  for( int j = 0; j \u003c sizeof(hashtype); j++ )\n  {\n    uint8_t b;\n    memcpy (\u0026b, \u0026hashval, 1);\n    counts[ b ]++;\n    hashval \u003e\u003e= 8;\n  }\n```\nshould be inside the `for (uint32_t seed = 0; seed \u003c 1\u003c\u003c31; seed += 8) {}` loop. Everything else should be outside of this loop.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1598320793,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3OTQ1NzI3Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-679457276"},"message":"@rurban Note that in BitFreq branch you are applying the test to Seed parameter variation. So, this test will only tell how much the hash function is good as a random number generator. The same `bitfreq` test is best applied to the proposed `sparse long` and `Words` tests as well.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599020531,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY4NTI4NTM3OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-685285379"},"message":"@rurban Here is a lot better normalcy estimator. I think all good hash functions pass it anyway, but `fabs( devsq - 1.0 )` has a lot stricter range here, values \u003e0.15 is a fail.\n```\ninit:\n\tconst int BitPoolSizeX = 10;\n\tconst int BitPoolSize = 1 \u003c\u003c BitPoolSizeX;\n\tconst int BitPoolSizeMask = BitPoolSize - 1;\n\tuint64_t BitCounts[ BitPoolSize ] = { 0 };\n\tint BitPoolPos = 0;\n\nupdate:\n\t\tint j;\n\n\t\tfor( j = 0; j \u003c HashLen; j++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tuint8_t v = Hash[ j ];\n\t\t\tint k;\n\n\t\t\tfor( k = 0; k \u003c 8; k++ )\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\tBitCounts[ BitPoolPos ] += v \u0026 1;\n\t\t\t\tBitPoolPos = ( BitPoolPos + 1 ) \u0026 BitPoolSizeMask;\n\t\t\t\tv \u003e\u003e= 1;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\nfinal:\n\tuint64_t AvgI = 0;\n\n\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c BitPoolSize; i++ )\n\t{\n\t\tAvgI += BitCounts[ i ];\n\t}\n\n\tdouble Avg = (double) AvgI / BitPoolSize;\n\tdouble devsq = 0.0;\n\n\tfor( i = 0; i \u003c BitPoolSize; i++ )\n\t{\n\t\tconst double d = BitCounts[ i ] / Avg - 1.0;\n\t\tdevsq += d * d;\n\t}\n\n\tdevsq *= 2.0 * Avg / BitPoolSize;\n```","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599536532,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY4ODYwMDU2Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/139#issuecomment-688600566"},"message":"@rurban Here's a lot better variant, works better since bit buffer length is a prime number.\n\ninit:\n\tconst int BitPoolSize = 1021;\n\tuint64_t BitCounts[ BitPoolSize ] = { 0 };\n\tint BitPoolPos = 0;\n\nupdate:\n\t\tint j;\n\n\t\tfor( j = 0; j \u003c HashLen; j++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tuint8_t v = Hash[ j ];\n\t\t\tint k;\n\n\t\t\tfor( k = 0; k \u003c 8; k++ )\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\tBitCounts[ BitPoolPos ] += v \u0026 1;\n\t\t\t\tBitPoolPos++;\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tif( BitPoolPos == BitPoolSize )\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tBitPoolPos = 0;\n\t\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\t\tv \u003e\u003e= 1;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599536532,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk4NDU1NzU4"},"target":"43a2720462ca5d0c03795ae48530041dd96832f5f92aea662294baf033e346e5","message":"@rurban Here's a lot better variant, works better since bit buffer length is a prime number.\n```\ninit:\n\tconst int BitPoolSize = 1021;\n\tuint64_t BitCounts[ BitPoolSize ] = { 0 };\n\tint BitPoolPos = 0;\n\nupdate:\n\t\tint j;\n\n\t\tfor( j = 0; j \u003c HashLen; j++ )\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tuint8_t v = Hash[ j ];\n\t\t\tint k;\n\n\t\t\tfor( k = 0; k \u003c 8; k++ )\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\tBitCounts[ BitPoolPos ] += v \u0026 1;\n\t\t\t\tBitPoolPos++;\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\tif( BitPoolPos == BitPoolSize )\n\t\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\t\tBitPoolPos = 0;\n\t\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\t\tv \u003e\u003e= 1;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n```","files":null}]}